article.headline: Utah Valley St. 85, CS Bakersfield 74
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 32 points and Utah Valley State made 13 of 16 free throws in the final 2:30 to beat Cal State Bakersfield 85-74 on Saturday. Toolson made all 10 of his free throw attempts and hit six 3-pointers for the Wolverines (7-13). Jordan Brady scored 13 points and Richard Troyer and Josh Olsen added 11 apiece. Donavan Bragg led the Roadrunners with 17 points, reserve Alex Johnson scored 15 and Donald Lee also came off the bench and scored 14. Utah Valley State took its first lead of the second half after a Toolson jumper with 15:42 to play and led by 10 with 7:10 to go. Cal State Bakersfield ran off seven consecutive points to pull with three with 5:51 to go, but the Wolverines' free-throw shooting kept the Roadrunners from getting any closer.
